 44 as some suggest for the 3 hit evade chain from CS. I could spend the extra pts into stealth/dw.<br>
<br>
I'll be taking thrust to 50 either way.<br>
<br>
My question is there is a 4 hit evade chain ratfang/beartooth/liontooth/wyvernfang in the thrust line.  Does the full chain not do enough damage to be viable compared to the CS evade chain, or does the stun on ratfang negate/hinder the Dragonfang stun? Just curious why no one seems to talk about it.<br>
<br>
Anyone tested this? or could test this for me? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/unandurius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nandurius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 8:31:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3717.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/phaas/phazer-avatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evade Chains</span><hr size=1> You want 50 thrust, 39 crit. Use the extra points to boost DW or whatever =D<br>
<br>
<br>
Attack chains:<br>
<br>
1) Light targets: Perf, CD, SS, then either let lifebane finish, or finish with garrote/ah.<br>
<br>
2) Heavy targets: Perf, Dragonfang+tranquilize, Dragonfang+wyvernfang, (tranq and wyvernfang are backup styles.) until dragonfang sticks, then use hamstring, leaper, hamstring, leaper.<br>
<br>
The detaunt tranqulize has no bonus damage, but a high bonus to defense. This causes other players to MISS you (it may also improve your chance to evade, but evades happen so often this is hard to judge.) Wyvernfang has nice bonus damage (+70-ish) and an attack speed debuff.<br>
You should land DF within 2-3 rounds (~75 bonus damage) and then hamstring/leaper will hit for 80-90 style damage each, twice.<br>
<br>
Unlike garrote, this is very endurance effective =P<br>
<br>
You're right about the thrust-evade chain stun, it will set off the one-minute stun immunity with the short stun (3s.) <br>
<br>
I logged/parsed some style damage while fighting in DF, this may give you an approx. idea of style bonus damage of the thrust styles up to 50, and cs up to 39. Only interesting to see how styles compare to each other, ignore the actual damage numbers they depend on so many factors (mob/player, weaponskill, weapons, item bonuses etc.)<br>
