 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/udaocfom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>daoc fom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 9:39:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3717.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wyvernfang</span><hr size=1> Unless I'm wrong ( I hope I am) wyvernfang is a chain off style that requires a parry.<br>
<br>
I do want to try the tranquilize, I don't have DF, I wonder if using hamstring+tranquilize, to get more evades then using the ham+leaper to kill the prey when I solo would work, hmm...<br>
<br>
<br>
Aleth<br>
3x Infil on Isu.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uxkobo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xkobo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 10:20:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3717.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evade Chains</span><hr size=1> The 3 hit evade chain is difficult to accomplish and in my opinion, not worth the skill points.<br>
<br>
The chain also uses 3 hotkey positions.  In my pvp combat setup, my hotkey bar only holds 1 style based off of evade. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulandril77.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Landril77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/10/02 2:52:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3717.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Evade Chains</span><hr size=1> The evade chain is by far the most efficient damage an infiltrator can do.  The thrust evade chain is a joke.  The damage on it is pathetic.<br>
<br>
It is very easy to get the evade chain off.  This is especially true if you are using it to follow up dragonfang.  Without the evade chain my infiltrator would have been retired ages ago.<br>
<br>
I think the main reason most people dislike the evade chain is that they use gar/AH as their any time attack.  The defensive penalty on garrote reduces your evade percentage dramatically so you do not evade nearly as often.  By not useing gar/ah and instead giving up a little damage in favor of defensive bonuses I cannot remember the last time I had a fight in which I did not evade at least one attack.  Once you evade once you can live on the evade chain for the remainder of the fight.  Dragonfang, hamstring, leaper, hamstring, leaper, rib separator, ripper can all be done off of a single evade.  These styles also give a defensive bonus promoting more evades once the chain is begun.<br>
<br>
I have no difficulty keeping hotkey room for the evade chain.  I have my opening moves on my first page of HK's which has PA, CD, SS, Tanqualize, Wyvernfang, stick, stealth and sprint.  Then my second page is for combat after the opening tranq, wyvern,dragonfang, ham, leaper, rib seperator stick, stealth(only have 47CS so I don't have Ripper or I would drop wyvernfang to make room for it.  I also have a combat bank which has Gar/AH in place of tran/wyvern for times when I just need to do damage in a hurry and get out, but it is rarely used.<br>
<br>
Wyvernfang is not part of the thrust evade chain, it chains off tranqualize and does similar damage to garrote without the high endurance cost or defensive penalties.  I use this chain in place of Gar/ah because the damage loss is not that much, it uses much less endurance, and having a defensive bonus rather than a defensive penalty helps ensure that I evade a rediculous amount of attacks.<br>
<br>
Despite the effectivness of dragonfang, Once respec is in I will most likely be changing to slash spec because amethyst slash/diamond slash would allow me to do better anytime damage without taking the defensive penalties associated with gar/ah.  Also, chain classes are becoming much less viable targets with epic armor, purge and IP in the game, so I am going to work towards killing other assassins and archers more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=3717.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=3717.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3717.topic&index=4><img src=http://216.40.211.42/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=3717.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=3717.topic><img src=http://216.40.211.42/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3717.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3717.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cells